he state-of-the-art could look completely different.&#160;</span></p><p sty=
le=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0=
 0 20px 0;"><strong>Still, immune cells are only a single facet of the broa=
der cell-based therapy revolution.</strong></p><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 6=
4, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>In m=
odern biotech, analogies to computer science aren&#8217;t metaphorical. The=
 induced pluripotent stem cell (iPSC) revolution makes this crystal clear. =
iPSC technology takes advantage of the beautiful nature of human developmen=
t. We all begin life as a single cell and undergo genetically </span><em>pr=
ogrammed</em><span> rounds of cell division. Most cells differentiate into =
a final cell type, like skin, lung, heart, and brain cells. Some cells don&=
#8217;t. These cells&#8212;called stem cells&#8212;occupy certain niches in=
 the body, and can be stimulated to differentiate into multiple cell types,=
 like a versatile back-up player. In 2006, a research paper from the lab of=
 a Japanese stem cell scientist named Shinya Yamanaka demonstrated a result=
 that bordered on absurd: </span><strong>using a tiny cocktail consisting o=
f only four genes, it&#8217;s possible to </strong><em><strong>reprogram</s=
trong></em><strong> differentiated cells into &#8220;pluripotent&#8221; ste=
m cells that can be differentiated into other cell types.</strong></p><p st=
yle=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0 0 20px 0;"><span>Think about that. Your skin cell, transformed into a neu=
ron. Or muscle cells. Or heart cells. This simple set of genes called &#822=
0;reprogramming factors&#8221; (also referred to as Yamanaka factors) laid =
the basis for the field of iPSC engineering. Now, scientists around the wor=
ld are working to perfect the right </span><em>cellular programs</em><span>=
 to convert iPSCs into every other cell type in the body. This has two imme=
diate ramifications for medicine:</span></p><ol style=3D"margin-top: 0; pad=
ding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=3D"box-sizing: borde=
r-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-height: 26px; margin: =
0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>iPSCs as a model system to=
 study disease.</strong></p></li><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p sty=
le=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>iPS=
