: 26px; margin: 0; margin-bottom: 0; padding-left: 4px;"><strong>Cells</str=
ong></p></li></ol><p style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line=
-height: 26px; margin: 0 0 20px 0;"><span>CAR-T does represent an entirely =
new type of medicine. But the GLP-1 example illustrates that there could be=
 real benefits to having cells produce big molecules based on smart detecti=
on of signals inside the body. Couldn&#8217;t this also logically extend to=
 small molecules? After all, some of our best small molecules are things th=
at we </span><a href=3D"https://substack.com/redirect/cb587cdd-6d22-4689-95=
8d-aa94af2a50ff?j=3DeyJ1IjoiOXAwZ3QifQ.gb8J5T7GnA_ZlNuaMZjmlXXepKbqOsa8-6m8=
ExkRNpU" rel style=3D"color: rgb(64, 64, 64); text-decoration: underline;">=
discovered being produced by cells in the first place</a><span>. So, in tim=
e, everything could become a subset of cell therapy:</span></p><ol style=3D=
"margin-top: 0; padding: 0;"><li style=3D"margin: 8px 0 0 32px;"><p style=
=3D"box-sizing: border-box; color: rgb(64, 64, 64); font-size: 16px; line-h=
